             // -rpcport was specified
-            const uint16_t rpcport_int{ToIntegral<uint16_t>(rpcport_arg.value()).value_or(0)};
+            const uint16_t rpcport_int = static_cast<uint64_t>(rpcport_arg.value()) > std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max() ? 0 : rpcport_arg.value();
             if (rpcport_int == 0) {
                 // Uses argument provided as-is
                 // (rather than value parsed)
```
Again:
```
₿ bitcoin-cli -noconf getblockcount
0
```
Hm... Tempted to apply `DISALLOW_NEGATION` to `-conf` here as well, but I guess skipping having a configuration file is allowable. It turns out `-conf` uses the only place currently calling `IsArgNegated` outside of tests:
```C++
fs::path ArgsManager::GetPathArg(std::string arg, const fs::path& default_value) const
{
    if (IsArgNegated(arg)) return fs::path{};
```
Outer context is:
```C++
bool ArgsManager::ReadConfigFiles(std::string& error, bool ignore_invalid_keys)
{
    {
        LOCK(cs_args);
        m_settings.ro_config.clear();
        m_config_sections.clear();
